COMPILE information
-the code was compiled and tested using gcc 11.4.0 and the C++ 20 standard on linux
-to compile the code the command make Assement1 should be used
-to clean the binaries the command make clean should be used 

setup.txt
-the system can be modified in setup.txt
-you can change the start and end mass and spring constant and change the step between them
-you can change the name of the output file and the system tolerance

plotting
-plotting is handled by PLOTTING.py 
-running the command python3 plotting in the command line should run the python file

VISUAL STUDIO CODE
-if using visual studio code there are two .json files that enable easier debugging and the ability to run the code by pressing fn+f5, this will also compile the code if any changes have been made
